What is the projected market size & growth rate of the Data Center Virtualization Market?

Market Analysis and Insights :

Global Data Center Virtualization Market

The data center virtualization market is expected to witness market growth at a rate of 16.05% in the forecast period of 2021 to 2028. Data Bridge Market Research report on data center virtualization market provides analysis and insights regarding the various factors expected to be prevalent throughout the forecast period while providing their impacts on the market’s growth. The rise in the demand from various industry verticals is escalating the growth of data center virtualization market.

Data centers virtualization refers to a method of creating, implementing and developing a data center on cloud computing and virtualization technologies. The technology enables the virtualization of physical servers in a data center facility along with storage and networking, among other devices and equipment for infrastructure. The virtualization includes various tools and services that assist the datacentre to perform different functions.

The increase in data center complexities across the globe acts as one of the major factors driving the growth of data center virtualization market. The rise in need to reduce enterprise operational costs and enhance business agility, and increase in deployment of data center virtualization owning to various features such as reduction in cost, better testing, no vendor lock in, better disaster recovery, greener pastures, and easier migration of cloud among others accelerate the market growth. The surge in prevalence of unified and centralized management of data centers, and increase in demand for the technology as it optimizes resources form the infrastructure resource and further assists in declining operational cost and center capital further influence the market. Additionally, expansion of end use industries, increase in investments, rapid digitization and increase in number of data centers positively affect the data center virtualization market. Furthermore, increased adoption of private cloud and increased spending on data center technology extend profitable opportunities to the market players in the forecast period of 2021 to 2028.

On the other hand, data center localization and limitations associated with the virtualization of legacy IT infrastructure are expected to obstruct the market growth. Lack of awareness regarding virtualization technology is projected to challenge the data center virtualization market in the forecast period of 2021-2028.

